<br>
Whoa that might make a good title for Acturian..<br>
<br>
The Master EGO! heheh<br>
<br>
Anyhow, on another note:  It was mentioned in a post not far above this one that people used an individual's leaving as an excuse for leaving the guild and then later blamed the person for single handedly dividing it. <br>
<br>
The person is right, folks.. too many people really do do this. <br>
Just because one person leaves, does not mean a mass riot has to ensue.   A guild is something that is supposed to be made up of its follwers' ideas and ideals.... if your guild does not have a small part of you involved in it in any fashion, then it isn't your guild.. but don't be casting blame for your leaving on another person.    <br>
<br>
When I left Aetherium, if was because I flat decided it was not for me.   It did not reflect on my taste for individuality and so.. I moved on.  People that asked me about Aetherium recieved an &quot;It's a good guild, even though it is not my kind of guild.. it is still something that you should try.&quot;  But alas, it disbanded and when I got the news I felt really really sad, for it was, truely, a good guild while it was under recovery from its past.    <br>
<br>
I never asked Acturian to leave Aetherium with me.  I remember him sending me a tell saying that he felt that he wanted to be a builder, not a rebuilder and that he wanted to team up with me to create a new guild that would work with my personal, &quot;individuality&quot; rule.    <br>
I talked to Graybull and revieved a tell saying that he figured Acturian would leave when I left and the Paladin did not sound too happy about it at that moment.    <br>
Well, the guild was created and while it was still untagged we went through a lot to get it.  On my OWN INITIATIVE I created a site on EZboard for &quot;Chaotic Neutrality&quot;, which is what the guild was suposed to be named originally. Then all of a sudden we learned that someone had taken the name that I had spoken to a non-involved person about and turned it into a guild before we even got off the ground.   Thus, Acturian came up with a new name &quot;Anarchy Contained&quot;.  We hung arond for quite a while with our &quot;guild&quot; channel awaiting the day that Acturian would hold the tag, since it was agreed upon myself and Acturian that he would do so since we could not get dual leadership tags for the guild.  With the guild name changed, I created a new ezboard account and a new page to reflect the new guild name.  Everything seemed to be going very well and I was very happy with my co-leader.  Acturian had Jabker work on web design and we all got on MSN one day and revamped the forum to fit all of our needs, including changes of color because SOME people did not like my black and red.    <br>
<br>
Then something happened and Acturian had to leave for 3 months.. not one not two but THREE.   During that time, I held an officer tag and was in charge of making sure the guild remained a happy place.  Sour events ensued... I was at a guild sanctioned event and one of my members ninja looted an item from someone who had come to help us at our request ,whom we allowed to roll on loot along with us, fairly.  <br>
I told them that they needed to repair the guild by camping the mob again and getting an item off that mob to that person, of the person's choice. Some of us actually stayed, but when the time came.. noone was there.   Acturian did some &quot;investigative&quot; research and learned that Gnibblet aka Raiding had told the person that if they did not ninja the piece that he would kick them out of the guild, and so the person listened to him instead of me because my tag did not say &quot;leader&quot; on it at that time, even though that was my function.   It ended up with me kicking some people out, recieving tells against those people and more tells about some other people in my guild, which I kicked out.   This after we had lost about 5 members(not the people I kicked out) allready due to the guild's prior indescretion on who to accept into membership.   <br>
<br>
Later, Acturian shows up in game and tells me that he wants his stuff back, so I go and meet with him and return his gear. Then without warning he boots me from the guild.   He tells me &quot; I'm sorry but I have to sort this mess out.&quot;.   I am in shock.   Here I was the  co-leader of a guild I created, having worked my ass off to gain new membership to replace the ninjalotting, scamming, hacking element that was once there, and now I was standing there, no tag, unwanted, and feeling very very much used.   A short time later I got invited back into the guild as a member with an apology.  <br>
<br>
Acturian sent me an email.  He told me that Gnibblet had stolen his account and asked me to get on and change his password before it was to late.   I told him what I would change the pw to  in an email but then the next day, Acturian &quot;Real Acturian&quot; was back, so it was never needed.   Acturian told me this story about how he got a whole bunch of RL information on Gnibblet and scared the heck out of him and got his account back... blah blah blah.   <br>
<br>
I deleted all of Acturian's prior emails to me and so I was without his account info from then on.    I told Acturian never to share that info again, because I thought that perhaps that that mess was enough for him to learn his lesson.   <br>
<br>
Next thing I know... Acturian talked to all of the people I had kicked out, reinvited those that would come back and accused me of &quot;kicking out half of the guild&quot;.  Even though I had replaced every member that I kicked out with someone respectable and even gained some more people to replace those that had left on their own initiative.   <br>
<br>
Things went from bad, to worse.  Acturian told me to &quot;let me handle everything&quot; and pretty nearly did everything except kick me out of the guild. I took a drop back to member with my own decision and then eventually I left, because it was no longer a reflection of my work, but something twisted. <br>
<br>
I had changed my password at least once per day after the climax of the mess.  I took a long vacation followed by another vacation.  I talked to Acturian and he was so, rude and full of malice and conceit that I realized that his and my relationship was like a grape run over by a dump truck.   Now came the feelings of abandonment, abuse, and for lack of a better word... betrayal. <br>
<br>
So that is what Acturian's and my relationship had grown to be.. what was once a friendship was now a relationship of.. betrayal.   That shit hurt.<br>
<br>
<br>
I waited a while, I saw that soemone had tried to ban me from the forum I created, so I banned everyone that was using the forum deleted everything and deleted the guildpage, changing the passwords to all.  I had wanted to give Acturian a friendly hello to let him know I was back in the occifer section but my discovery kinda made my decision for me.  Of course flames followed.. Acturian knew exactly who did it because I left a message. &quot;Welcome to Anarchy Contained, we should have been deleted.&quot;  He and a few of his members informed me in the flames that they had been setting up a new page and forum before my mass deletion and that my action was futile.  But, I tend to wonder why flame me if I was helping them by deleting the old junkpile?<br>
 <br>
Now, through my chain of information I have learned that the Anarchy Contained tag has not been seen for a while.  And I see in the boards that Acturian is in a new guild.  I hope that he is doing better this time and that his ego has gone down a few notches. It is unlikely, but it is still a wish of mine. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
